Leasing Bancolombia Sells 500 Billion Pesos of Securities

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-05-25T19:24:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/leasing-bancolombia-sells-500-billion-pesos-of-securities.html
Leasing Bancolombia SA, the leasing
arm of  Colombia ’s biggest lender, sold 500 billion pesos ($272.9
million) of bonds in the local market.  The Medellin-based financial company sold five- and 10.5-
year fixed-rate securities to yield 8.04 and 9.05 percent,
respectively, Colombia’s stock exchange said in a statement. The
company also sold 1.5- and three-year debt to yield 1.44 and
1.75 percentage points above the nation’s IBR interbank rate.  Leasing Bancolombia also sold two-year bonds to yield 1.9
percentage points above the DTF interbank rate, and 10-year
securities to yield 1.75 percentage points above inflation,
according to the stock exchange. Investor demand for the
securities equaled 717.4 billion pesos, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
